{
  "texts": [
    "Considering smart environments, ChatGPT has been used for zero-shot activity recognition [48].",
    "However, this work assumes the availability of several sensors capturing the interaction of the subject with many household items (e.g., specific food ingredients), which is unrealistic in real-world deployments.",
    "In this work, we consider a more realistic setting considering the sensors that are usually deployed in smart homes for ADL recognition (e.g., motion sensors, magnetic sensors, plug sensors).",
    "Finally, another work uses an LLM to provide a label to each cluster of raw sensor data time windows (collected in an initial deployment phase) [22].",
    "A supervised classifier is then trained using the pseudo-labels obtained through the LLM."
  ]
}